RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 77. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 23500. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING 10,000 FOR HORSES THAT HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 7 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BILL'S HONOR set the pace from between rivals, took the rail into the bend, was roused nearing the end of a half mile, drew off in the lane under urging and was clearly best. TRUIST prominent from outside, went for the lead three wide on the turn then battled to keep second in the stretch. ON THE MONEY RED bumped from the rear at the break, pressed in tight quarters between rivals on the backstretch, did not keep up on the bend, fanned four wide into the lane and was closing in for second late. RUN THE TABLE pressed in tight quarters along the rail, was steadied as he brushed repeatedly with ON THE MONEY RED from the half mile marker to the seven-sixteenths pole, was checked at that point, altered out, came five wide into the stretch and rallied belatedly. DIAMND CON SUERTE reluctant to load, hesitated slightly then broke somewhat awkwardly, stayed off the rail then closed well from path three deep stretch. XPRESSIR boxed in while in close quarters on the backstretch, gained a clear path into the turn, went for the lead just outside BILL'S HONOR but could not sustain his bid in the lane. J J'S SOLUTION failed to be a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: RUMBRANDT was kept close, angled to the outside on the bend, came five wide into the lane, lugged in beside DEVIL upper stretch, edged ahead slightly as she jostled with the latter the rest of the way and held on. DEVIL vied for the lead between horses, came into the stretch from path three, exchanged bumps with RUMBRANDT the last furlong and had to settle for second best. BEEHIVE contested the pace between rivals, gained the rail on the bend then slowly wore down deep stretch. BAR MONEY well back early, picked up her pace along the rail on the turn, lost ground fanning widest for the stretch run, surged the final furlong but was too late. GREEN GRACE disputed the pace between horses, was shuffled back while two wide on the bend, moved to the rail into the lane, was blocked nearing the sixteenth marker, altered out and finished evenly. CLOEY ATTACK vied for the lead from outside, came four wide into the lane, began to yield, altered out when RUMBRANDT took her path upper stretch and continued to slowly fade. TOO MUCH TUESDAY displayed early speed from inside, was steadied back from tight quarters nearing the bend, altered out and steadily gave way. The rider of DEVIL lodged an objection alleging interference from RUMBRANDT the last eighth. After their review, the stewards did not uphold that claim of foul.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JACK SPRAT was steadied repeatedly while boxed in behind the early speed on the backstretch, moved to the rail into the bend, checked briefly when his path narrowed leaving the turn, squeezed through along the rail upper stretch then drew off inside the last eighth. TIGGER ATTACK flipped in the gate before the start, was taken out, okayed by the veterinarian after examination then showed little racing widest once the race began. RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 9 6F Dirt CR: 76. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 26500. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER OR WAIVER CLAIMING OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $12,500 FOR HORSES W HICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 7 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BE MY BESTIE broke inward, bumping STACY ATTACK, was corrected, advanced from inside, was steadied while boxed in behind the leaders on the bend, got through two wide upper stretch, moved clear and held sway under urging. MOON PIES IMAGE without early speed, picked up her pace from path three on the turn, moved out six wide upper stretch for a clear path, rallied inside CAHOKIA POSSE and got the nod for second at the wire. CAHOKIA POSSE also without early speed, commenced her bid from outside on the bend, fanned out six wide entering the lane, angled out some as MOON PIES IMAGE came out upper stretch, rallied with that one in the late going and narrowly missed second. JULYNNE raced in contention from outside, angled in between horses with four furlongs to go, was three to five wide taking the turn and slowly wore down through the waning yards. CANDY LOOKER in the second flight early, went for the lead three wide on the bend, fanned out some for the stretch run and began to wear down. STACY ATTACK was bumped from the rear at the break, disputed the pace outside BIG SALLY, moved ahead two wide on the turn, floated out slightly at the top of the lane and faded the last furlong. BIG SALLY a step slow at the start, moved up quickly from inside to vie for the lead but began to fade before finishing a half mile. SHINE DOWN reared up at the break and was always outrun. DELTA LADY was reluctant to load, fractious in the gate, was rearing up as the gate opened and her rider dismounted. There was a stewards' inquiry into DELTA LADY'S start. After their review, it was determined that DELTA LADY was not prepared to race when the gate opened and she was declared a non-starter for pari-mutuel purposes only. A consolation Daily Double was paid and all wagers, except the Pick 3 were refunded.
